# Setup New Page Sub-Skill

## Overview

This sub-skill guides the human to create the `/midtempo-framework/instructions/new-page.md` file through structured dialogue and codebase analysis.

**Goal:** Create new-page.md documenting how to wire a new page/screen into the application with verification gates for routing, navigation, data loading, and error handling.

**Scope:** This file documents PAGE/SCREEN WIRING (routing, navigation, data flow, error handling). 

---

## The Process

### Non-Negotiable Rules

<CRITICAL_REQUIREMENT type="MANDATORY">

- You MUST read `/midtempo-framework/instructions/architecture.md` and `/midtempo-framework/instructions/frontend-design.md` to understand the repo's structure
- You MUST identify routing mechanism (React Router, Vue Router, Angular Router, UINavigationController, Navigation Component, etc.)
- You MUST identify navigation patterns (nav components, tab bars, drawers, etc.)
- You MUST identify data loading patterns (loaders, hooks, ViewModels, repositories)
- You MUST draft sections based on evidence from code
- You MUST present each drafted section for validation before proceeding
- You MUST write validated content to `/midtempo-framework/instructions/new-page.md` incrementally
- You MUST perform alignment check before marking complete
- You MUST follow the `/midtempo-framework/rules/writing.md` rules
- You MUST use UK English spelling throughout
- You MUST focus on WIRING PATTERNS and RULES, not implementation details
- You MUST limit scope to page WIRING verification (route, component, navigation, data, error handling, files)

</CRITICAL_REQUIREMENT>

