## Phase 1: UI Framework Detection

**Do not skip to questions.** Detect UI framework and patterns first.

### 1.1 Agent Actions (Silent)

```
SEARCH for UI framework indicators:
  - React: *.jsx, *.tsx with JSX syntax, react imports, components/
  - Vue: *.vue files, vue imports, components/
  - Angular: *.component.ts, @angular imports, app/
  - SwiftUI: *.swift with View protocol, @State, NavigationView
  - Kotlin: *.kt with @Composable, Jetpack Compose imports
  - UIKit: *.swift with UIViewController, storyboards/
  - Android Views: *.kt with Activity, Fragment, layouts/
  - Server templates: *.ejs, *.pug, *.erb, *.jinja2, views/

IDENTIFY routing mechanism:
  - React: react-router-dom (Route, Routes), Next.js (app/, pages/), Remix (routes/)
  - Vue: vue-router (createRouter), Nuxt (pages/)
  - Angular: @angular/router (RouterModule, routes)
  - SwiftUI: NavigationStack, NavigationLink
  - UIKit: UINavigationController, segues, storyboards
  - Jetpack Compose: Navigation Component, NavHost, composable()
  - Android Views: Intent navigation, FragmentManager
  - Server: Express routes, Rails routes.rb, Django urls.py

IDENTIFY navigation patterns:
  - Web: Nav components, sidebars, headers, breadcrumbs
  - Mobile: Tab bars, navigation bars, drawers, bottom navigation
  - Location: Dedicated nav components or inline per page

IDENTIFY data loading patterns:
  - React: useEffect, loaders (Remix/React Router), getServerSideProps (Next.js)
  - Vue: onMounted, asyncData (Nuxt), route guards
  - Angular: Resolvers, ngOnInit
  - SwiftUI: onAppear, @StateObject with ViewModel
  - UIKit: viewDidLoad with service calls
  - Jetpack Compose: LaunchedEffect, ViewModel with StateFlow
  - Android Views: onCreate with ViewModel or direct calls

IDENTIFY page structure patterns:
  - File naming: PascalCase, kebab-case, snake_case
  - Directory structure: Flat, nested by feature, nested by type
  - Page templates: Layouts, wrappers, common structure
  - Scaffolding tools: CLI generators, templates

FIND testing patterns for pages:
  - Unit tests: Component/screen rendering tests
  - Integration tests: Navigation flow tests
  - E2E tests: Full user journey tests
  - Test file location: Co-located, separate test directories
```

