3. Navigation Integration

3.1 Navigation component location

`src/components/Navigation/NavBar.tsx`

3.2 Navigation type

Sidebar navigation with nested sections

3.3 Adding navigation entry

1. Add route config to `NAV_ITEMS` array in `src/config/navigation.ts`
2. Include icon from `react-icons`, label, path, and required permissions
3. Add E2E test for navigation link in `tests/e2e/navigation.test.ts`

3.4 Navigation structure

Nested by feature area (Admin, Projects, Settings)

3.5 Conditional navigation

Items filtered by `usePermissions()` hook

**Example navigation item**:

{
  label: 'User Profile',
  path: '/users/:userId',
  icon: FiUser,
  permissions: ['users.read'],
  section: 'admin'
}

3.6 Rules

- Only add to navigation if page is user-accessible (not API-only routes)
- Navigation items MUST include permission requirements
- Navigation order within sections MUST be alphabetical
- Active state styling handled automatically via `useLocation()`
- All navigation changes MUST have E2E test for link click
```

